.NET Framework 3.5.name: VRTK_ObjectAppearance
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: The Object Appearance script provides a collection of static methods for controlling the appearance of a GameObject.
.NET Framework 3.5.remarks: The GameObject can have it's opacity changed, or it's renderers toggled, or highlighters toggled.

methods.name: HighlightObject(GameObject model, Nullable<Color> highlightColor, float fadeDuration)
methods.summary: The HighlightObject method calls the Highlight method on the highlighter attached to the given GameObject with the provided colour.

params.value: The GameObject to attempt to call the Highlight on.
The duration in time to fade from the initial colour to the target colour.

methods.name: SetOpacity(GameObject model, float alpha, float transitionDuration)
methods.summary: The SetOpacity method allows the opacity of the given GameObject to be changed. A lower alpha value will make the object more transparent, such as 0.5f will make the controller partially transparent where as 0f will make the controller completely transparent.

params.value: The GameObject to change the renderer opacity on.
The alpha level to apply to opacity of the controller object. 0f to 1f.
The time to transition from the current opacity to the new opacity.

methods.syntax: public static void SetOpacity(GameObject model, float alpha, float transitionDuration)
methods.linkedSyntax: public static void SetOpacity(GameObject model, float alpha, float transitionDuration)

methods.name: SetRendererHidden(GameObject model, GameObject ignoredModel)
methods.summary: The SetRendererHidden method turns off renderers of a given GameObject. It can also be provided with an optional model to ignore the render toggle on.

params.value: The GameObject to hide the renderers for.
An optional GameObject to ignore the renderer toggle on.

methods.syntax: public static void SetRendererHidden(GameObject model, GameObject ignoredModel)
methods.linkedSyntax: public static void SetRendererHidden(GameObject model, GameObject ignoredModel)

methods.name: SetRendererVisible(GameObject model, GameObject ignoredModel)
methods.summary: The SetRendererVisible method turns on renderers of a given GameObject. It can also be provided with an optional model to ignore the render toggle on.

params.value: The GameObject to show the renderers for.
An optional GameObject to ignore the renderer toggle on.

methods.syntax: public static void SetRendererVisible(GameObject model, GameObject ignoredModel)
methods.linkedSyntax: public static void SetRendererVisible(GameObject model, GameObject ignoredModel)

methods.name: ToggleRenderer(bool state, GameObject model, GameObject ignoredModel)
methods.summary: The ToggleRenderer method turns on or off the renderers of a given GameObject. It can also be provided with an optional model to ignore the render toggle of.

params.value: If true then the renderers will be enabled, if false the renderers will be disabled.
The GameObject to toggle the renderer states of.
An optional GameObject to ignore the renderer toggle on.
